Modifications in this repository (see patches/ and gemma-nvfp4/) add AMD RDNA4
(gfx1201) enablement to vLLM 0.19.1 and are released under the same Apache License,
Version 2.0. Changes are delivered as patch files (diffs against the stated upstream
versions) and grafted source files that preserve the upstream copyright and SPDX
headers; the patches and this NOTICE are the record of what changed.

This repository also includes:

  * Code backported from vLLM 0.23.0 — the gemma4_assistant draft-model spec-decode
    (a Gemma4MTPModel / Gemma4AssistantForCausalLM class plus framework patches).
    Same upstream project, Apache-2.0; a newer revision than the 0.19.1 base.

  * A clean-room Triton re-implementation of a head-dim-512 flash-attention chunking
    technique whose blueprint comes from llama.cpp
    (https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp), MIT-licensed. No llama.cpp code was
    copied — only the algorithm/tile-configuration was used as a reference.

  * Forward-ported RDNA4 MXFP4 / NVFP4 kernel enablement derived from Rob Smith's
    tcclaviger/vllm-rocm-mxfp4-nvfp4 RDNA4 work.

Other components used or referenced (not modified, not redistributed here):

  * Triton / triton_kernels — MIT.
  * AMD ROCm (hipBLASLt, rocBLAS, RCCL, HIP) — MIT.
  * PyTorch — BSD-3-Clause (inherited via the base image).
  * HuggingFace Transformers — Apache-2.0 (inherited via the base image).

This is a build recipe; no model weights are included. Model weights are bind-mounted
at runtime from the user's own Hugging Face cache. Model families referenced
(Qwen3.5/3.6-MoE by Alibaba; Gemma-4 by Google; the RedHatAI NVFP4 quantization of
Gemma-4) are the property of their respective owners — confirm the license on the
specific model card you deploy.
